From Blaine Gardner Subject Re Boom Dog attack In article BONG BONG Eric Bong writes In article wrote What worked for me on my was to lean towards the dog as I modulated throttle to keep my ankle just ahead of his After a few seconds of warm pipe firmly wedged on his shoulder he turned his face sideways to see what was so warm and got his mouth nose muzzle burned on the A bicycling technique I've employed was to use my frame mounted tire pump to fend off dog One of my brothers had spent a lot of time practicing bizzare tricks on his megabuck micromass He said he once repelled a dog attack by picking up the rear of the bike and smacking the dog in the side of the head with the rear The dog had no idea what hit him and he fled quite Then again he could jump garbage cans without a ramp so I don't think I'd care to try this one on a The telephone worked much better than the tire That's almost unfair I've never seen a dog that could use a Blaine Gardner Evans Sutherland